            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="908" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d908">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/6–1746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-24T16:00:00-04:00">June 24, 1946—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1155. Following extracted from Shanghai’s tel 1076 June 18 (Deptel 1074 June
                        12<note n="34" xml:id="d908fn34">Not printed.</note> and Urtel 1908 June
                    17):</p>
                <pb facs="1187" n="1177" xml:id="pg_1177"/>
                <p>[Here follow first and second substantive paragraphs of telegram No. 1076, June
                    18, 11 a.m., <ref target="#pg_1175">page 1175</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Please take up with Fonoff by such means as you deem appropriate our desire to
                    commence operation at earliest possible date of radio transmitter at Dairen.
                    Point out inadequacy of present communications to and from Dairen. Say that with
                    concurrence Chinese Govt similar communication situation in certain other areas
                    of China has been remedied by our establishment of radio transmitters for
                    official use pending resumption of normal telecommunication facilities.</p>
                <p>Telegraph results of your representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
